Sure, here is an outline of the steps I would take to create a dropshipping business that generates at least $400 per month:

1. Choose a profitable niche: Before choosing a niche, I would conduct market research to identify profitable niches with high demand and low competition.

2. Identify suppliers: Once I have chosen a profitable niche, I would research and identify reliable, trustworthy suppliers with high-quality products at reasonable prices.

3. Choose an ecommerce platform: I would choose a dropshipping-friendly ecommerce platform such as Shopify, WooCommerce, or Magento to set up my online store.

4. Set up my store: I would design a professional-looking store with easy-to-navigate product categories, high-quality product images, and clear product descriptions.

5. Develop a marketing strategy: I would develop a marketing strategy to drive traffic to my store, including social media marketing, paid advertising, and content marketing.

6. Optimize conversions: I would optimize my website for conversions using tactics such as A/B testing, conversion rate optimization, and targeted landing pages.

7. Monitor metrics: I would monitor my store's metrics, such as traffic, sales, and conversion rates, to identify areas for improvement and make data-driven decisions.

As for creating a landing page code, here is a basic example of HTML and CSS I might use to create a simple, effective landing page:

<!DOCTYPE html>
<html>
<head>
	<title>My Landing Page</title>
	<style>
		body {
			background-color: #F7F7F7;
		}
		h1 {
			color: #333333;
			font-size: 36px;
			text-align: center;
			padding-top: 100px;
		}
		p {
			color: #666666;
			font-size: 24px;
			text-align: center;
			margin-top: 40px;
			margin-bottom: 40px;
		}
		button {
			background-color: #00BFFF;
			border: none;
			color: #FFFFFF;
			display: block;
			margin: 0 auto;
			padding: 20px 40px;
			font-size: 24px;
			border-radius: 5px;
			cursor: pointer;
			transition: all 0.3s ease;
		}
		button:hover {
			background-color: #0080FF;
			transform: translateY(-5px);
			box-shadow: 0px 5px 0px #0056B3;
		}
	</style>
</head>
<body>
	<h1>Welcome to My Landing Page</h1>
	<p>Here's a brief description of what my store offers. Lorem ipsum dolor sit amet, consectetur adipiscing elit. Nam eu justo enim. Sed vel pellentesque est. </p>
	<button>Call to Action Here</button>
</body>
</html>

Of course, this code is just an example and would need to be modified to fit a specific brand and product.
